{
  "a_galaxy_workflow": "true",
  "annotation": "Phase C, gene-projection half (split out of the former combined align_chain_project; the chaining half is now WF-C align_chain). Projects each anchor's gene annotation onto every query genome. CROSS_PRODUCT_FLAT builds the anchor x query grid as aligned lists, FILTER_FROM_FILE drops the anchor self cells (A_A, generated internally from the anchor element identifiers), then Liftoff -&gt; triage -&gt; merge map over the grid (Liftoff-only; TOGA2 off). Proven bit-identical to per-pair driving on the Pv4 test panel.",
  "comments": [],
